<hl>
<seg id=1> World Trade Organization and China Service Trade Discussion Meeting to Be Held in Shanghai </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua New Agency, Shanghai, April 15, Telegram (Reporter Xia Ruge and trainee Zhang Jiansong):  The "World Trade Organization and China Service Trade Discussion Meeting" will be opened in Shanghai on April 19.  The general secretary of the World Trade Organization, Lu Jieluo, will attend and give a special speech. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> It is reported that the main topic of the discussion meeting will be what sort of effect the promises China is making in the course of negotiations to enter the World Trade Organization to open up service trade industries such as finance, insurance, air shipment, information, the retail industry, advertising, lawyers, and accountants will have on counterpart domestic industries; what the international competitive strength of each industry is; and how the Chinese government can control the degree of opening up of the service trade during the course of negotiations. </seg>
<seg id=4> Additionally, the discussion meeting will explore the test establishment of a number of joint-investment enterprises in the area of foreign trade management in the future in Shanghai. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> This two-day meeting is being jointly held by the Shanghai Research Center of the World Trade Organization and the Shanghai Municipal Foreign Service Co., Ltd. </seg>
<seg id=6> Vice Minister Long Yongtu of the China Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, who accompanied Lu Jieluo to Shanghai, will also attend the discussion meeting. </seg>
<seg id=7> Additionally, members of the Foreign Economy and Trade Commissions of various provinces and cities of China, responsible persons at large enterprises, specialists, and academics - a total of 200 persons - [will] attend the discussion meeting. </seg>
</p>
